<p>Part of the new close process is to remove the Too Localized reason to close. The reasoning is given on <a href="https://meta.stackexchange.com/questions/185102/responding-to-your-too-localized-concerns">meta stackexchange</a>. The main reason is it is being misused on SO and a few other sites.</p>

<p>The question is what do we need to do on Ask Different, ask for TL to be kept or add more Off Topic reasons or what.....</p>

<p>I did a query for questions that we have closed as Too localised <a href="http://data.stackexchange.com/apple/query/120985/too-localised" rel="nofollow noreferrer">here</a></p>

